Date: Thu, 15 Jun 2017 22:42:06 -0700
Subject: Fix system panic when express lane enabled.
References: bsc#1044623
Patch-mainline: Submitted, http://marc.info/?l=linux-scsi&m=149759262410890&w=2

There is a null pointer dereference that can happen in the FOF interrupt
handler.

The driver was not setting up cq->assoc_qp_for sli4_hba->oas_cq.

Initialize cq->assoc_qp before accessing it.

Signed-off-by: Dick Kennedy <dick.kennedy@broadcom.com>
Signed-off-by: James Smart <james.smart@broadcom.com>
Signed-off-by: Johannes Thumshirn <jthumshirn@suse.de>
---
 drivers/scsi/lpfc/lpfc_sli.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/scsi/lpfc/lpfc_sli.c b/drivers/scsi/lpfc/lpfc_sli.c
index a657093a3bde..c99578bcf0f5 100644
--- a/drivers/scsi/lpfc/lpfc_sli.c
+++ b/drivers/scsi/lpfc/lpfc_sli.c
@@ -13564,6 +13564,9 @@ lpfc_sli4_fof_handle_eqe(struct lpfc_hba *phba, struct lpfc_eqe *eqe)
 		return;
 	}
 
+	/* Save EQ associated with this CQ */
+	cq->assoc_qp = phba->sli4_hba.fof_eq;
+
 	/* Process all the entries to the OAS CQ */
 	while ((cqe = lpfc_sli4_cq_get(cq))) {
 		workposted |= lpfc_sli4_fp_handle_cqe(phba, cq, cqe);
